# Excalidraw Architecture

## State Management

- Jotai atoms for global state (editor-jotai.ts) — NOT Redux/Zustand/MobX
- ActionManager (actions/manager.tsx) as command dispatcher for user actions
- State updates: actionManager.executeAction() or Jotai useSetAtom()
- State type: AppState (packages/excalidraw/types.ts)
- Default state: getDefaultAppState() in appState.ts

## Rendering

- Two-layer HTML5 Canvas 2D rendering — NOT React DOM for drawing
  - StaticCanvas: renders static elements via renderStaticScene()
  - InteractiveCanvas: handles pointer events, selection via renderInteractiveScene()
  - NewElementCanvas: renders elements being created in real-time
- RoughJS for hand-drawn sketch aesthetic
- Scene class (packages/element/src/Scene.ts) manages element arrays/maps
- DO NOT use react-konva, fabric.js, pixi.js

## Monorepo Structure

- packages/excalidraw/ — main editor library (App.tsx is the core component)
- packages/element/ — element definitions, Scene class
- packages/math/ — mathematical utilities
- packages/common/ — shared utilities, constants, types
- packages/utils/ — export utilities, shape helpers
- excalidraw-app/ — standalone web application

## Dependencies

- No new npm packages without explicit approval
- Check packages/common/ and packages/utils/ before adding external helpers
- Key deps: React 19, Jotai, RoughJS, Vite, Vitest

## How to verify

- `grep -r "from 'redux\|from 'zustand\|from 'mobx" packages/` — must return nothing
- `grep -r "react-konva\|fabric\.js\|pixi\.js" packages/` — must return nothing
- `yarn test:typecheck` — confirms no type errors from state/render changes
- `yarn test:app --watch=false` — confirms rendering pipeline still works